<section class="content-section" id="how-to-use"><h2>How to Use</h2><p>Answer 7 eligibility questions with Yes/No. The tool checks each criterion against <a href="https://www.startupindia.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DPIIT notification</a> dated February 2019 (as amended). Green = meets criteria, Red = does not meet. All 7 must be &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; for eligibility.</p><div class="callout"><p><strong>CA Tip:</strong> DPIIT recognition is separate from MSME/Udyam registration. You can and should get both. Startup India gives tax exemption under <a href="https://incometaxindia.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Section 80-IAC</a>, while MSME gives lending and procurement benefits. Our CAs at <a href="https://www.icai.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ICAI</a>-member firm can assist with both applications.</p></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="benefits"><h2>Startup India Benefits After DPIIT Recognition</h2><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="rate-table"><thead><tr><th>Benefit</th><th>Details</th><th>Section/Scheme</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Tax Exemption</td><td>100% profit deduction for 3 of first 10 years</td><td>Section 80-IAC</td></tr>
<tr><td>Angel Tax Exemption</td><td>No tax on share premium above FMV</td><td>Section 56(2)(viib)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Capital Gains Exemption</td><td>Exemption on investment in eligible startups</td><td>Section 54GB</td></tr>
<tr><td>Patent Fast-Track</td><td>80% rebate on patent fees + expedited exam</td><td>Patent Rules</td></tr>
<tr><td>Trademark Rebate</td><td>50% rebate on trademark filing fees</td><td>TM Rules</td></tr>
<tr><td>Self-Certification</td><td>No inspections for 3 years (6 labour + 3 env laws)</td><td>Startup India Action Plan</td></tr>
<tr><td>Seed Fund</td><td>Up to &#8377;50L through incubators</td><td>SISFS</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fund of Funds</td><td>&#8377;10,000 Cr through SIDBI-backed AIFs</td><td>FFS</td></tr>
</tbody></table></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="process"><h2>DPIIT Recognition Application Process</h2><ul><li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Register at <a href="https://www.startupindia.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">startupindia.gov.in</a> and create account</li><li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Fill recognition application with entity details, CIN/LLPIN, incorporation date</li><li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Upload Certificate of Incorporation and write-up of innovation (1&ndash;2 paragraphs)</li><li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Submit &mdash; DPIIT processes within 2&ndash;5 working days, no fee charged</li><li><strong>Step 5:</strong> Receive recognition certificate with unique Startup India recognition number</li><li><strong>Step 6:</strong> For 80-IAC tax benefit, apply separately to Inter-Ministerial Board with audited financials</li></ul></section>

<section class="content-section" id="comparison"><h2>Startup India vs MSME/Udyam &mdash; Which to Get?</h2><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="rate-table"><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Startup India (DPIIT)</th><th>MSME (Udyam)</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Eligibility</td><td>&lt; 10 years, &lt; &#8377;100Cr TO, innovation</td><td>Investment &amp; turnover based</td></tr>
<tr><td>Entity Types</td><td>Pvt Ltd, LLP, Partnership only</td><td>All including sole prop</td></tr>
<tr><td>Tax Benefit</td><td>80-IAC: 3 years 100% profit exemption</td><td>No direct tax benefit</td></tr>
<tr><td>Lending</td><td>Fund of Funds (indirect)</td><td>CGTMSE, priority lending</td></tr>
<tr><td>Procurement</td><td>Public procurement exemption</td><td>25% govt procurement reserved</td></tr>
<tr><td>Registration Fee</td><td>Free</td><td>Free</td></tr>
<tr><td>Recommendation</td><td colspan="2"><strong>Get BOTH &mdash; they are complementary, not exclusive</strong></td></tr>
</tbody></table></div></section>

